basics.name: Jonathan Na
basics.label: Graduate Student
basics.summary: Welcome to my portfolio! I am graduate student in M.S. in Computer Science in the Department of Information and Computer Sciences at the University of Hawaii. Come look at my various projects ranging from web applicatiosn to VR below.

work.summary: Responsible for analyzing overhead and aerial imagery developed by photographic and electronic means. Provided Army personnel with critical information about enemy forces, potential battle areas and combat operations support with a (inactive) TS/SCI Clearance.
highlights: Process, Exploitation, and Dissemination (PED) on: MSI, HSI, LIDAR, and SAR
highlights2: Conducted Full Motion Video (FMV) analysis in high ops tempo intelligence fusion environment with a (inactive) TS/SCI Clearance.
highlights3: Worked in a collaborative team environment with sudden fasts sprints with a strict SOP: Standard Operating Procedure.

publications.name: SAGE XR
publications.summary: Capstone research paper for ICS 699 project on the implementation of the Scalable Amplified Group Environment Extended Reality (SAGE XR). The goal of the project is to bring a tiled wall display and desktop environment into a VR platform.

publications.name: Moon Mission VR
publications.summary: A VR game/simulator for a spaceship mission to reach the moon based off the challenger center mission, using Unity in C# and the HTC VIVE with a team. I created the majority of the VR features ranging from the design, sound, lighting, trigger events and interaction.

publications.name: Evolutionary Computation with a Maze
publications.summary: Research paper for ICS 674 final project on the research to explore the use of genetic algorithms to create computational agents that navigate mazes, with an examination of the performance of the variation operators and evaluation between two different types of fitness search space.
